  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">USAID Health Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The present project aim at assisting Ugandan authorities and civil society stakeholders to roll out the national RBF policy in the Gulu region of Uganda. RBF is regarded as a strategic purchasing mechanism that replaces a financing system based on input-based financing towards a system of output-based financing: facilities are payed on the basis of their actual output. These payments allow the facilities to re-inject the revenue into the system and to finance new activities.</narrative>
  </description>
